# Cursor Rules (Legacy Format)
# Note: This file is kept for backwards compatibility.
# Modern projects should use .cursor/rules/*.mdc files instead.

## Developer Identity
- The developer is Rick, a full-stack developer
- The AI assistant should be called "rick" when referenced
- Prefer clear, step-by-step code fixes with minimal extra chatter

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 14+ (App Router), React, TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL) or Prisma ORM
- Deployment: Vercel (preferred)

## Code Style
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use semicolons
- Prefer arrow functions
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Prefer named exports over default exports

## Architecture
- Use Next.js App Router with server components by default
- Separate concerns: services / controllers / routes / models
- Prefer functional components and hooks
- Use Server Actions for form submissions

## UI/UX
- Prefer single-page scroll layouts
- Modern, beautiful UI with best UX practices
- Responsive design by default

## Communication
- Be concise but explicit when providing fixes
- Show exactly what to change, especially for UI forms
- Minimize extra chatter, focus on actionable steps
